cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.PL 

This paper is primarily focused on database security and access control mechanisms, which falls under the category of cs.DB (Database). However, the paper also discusses the limitations of existing access control mechanisms and the need for a stronger theoretical foundation for database security, which could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper presents a new access control mechanism that is provably secure, which could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
